  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u2019\u2019\u0dab\u0dba \u0d9c\u0dd9\u0dc0\u0dd3\u0db8\u0da7 \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dd2\u0db8 \u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dc1\u0dca\u0db1\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca \u0db1\u0dd1\u2019\u2019",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "\"There is no problem in paying the debt\"",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Mr. Ajith Nivard Kabral, Minister of State for Finance, Capital Market and Public Enterprise Reform, says that there is no problem in paying the loan money taken from abroad and their interest and the government has made all arrangements to pay that money at the end of this month.",
        "The Minister of State for Finance said that the opposition is sending a bad message to the international community that Sri Lanka is unable to pay its debts and said that what they are doing is very ugly.",
        "He also said that the opposition is telling that story to discourage investors who are hoping to come to Sri Lanka.",
        "Mr. Cabral said that what the opposition is saying is a false story and that the current government has paid all the debts on time.",
        "He said that the government has the ability to pay the debt no matter what anyone says and he also asked the opposition to refrain from making such treacherous statements against the country.",
        "However, he said that he admits that there is a problem in finding dollars and that the previous government handed over to the current government only a foreign reserve of seven billion US dollars.",
        "Mr. Ajith Nivard Kabral said that there is economic pressure in the face of the Covid epidemic and the government has somehow controlled the problem by facing the pressure.",
        "The Minister of State for Finance also stated that except for the import of vehicles, all other activities will be carried out as usual during a crisis.",
        "Mr. Cabral said that during the normal state of the country, more than 400 crores of rupees were received from the tourism industry and revealed that the income has now dropped to 50 crores of rupees."
      ],
